{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959638,"pPcc":"SAT#Q","questionId":"7b65bb28","skill_cd":"Q.C.","score_band_range_cd":5,"skill_desc":"One-variable data: Distributions and measures of center and spread","createDate":1691007959638,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Problem-Solving and Data Analysis","ibn":"10941-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"Q","uId":"5c4df776-aff2-41c0-922f-772334ca05d4","difficulty":"M"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"10941-DC","section":"Math","body":"<div xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p1\" class=\"stimulus_reference \">\n        <div class=\"table_wrapper \">\n          <table class=\"table\">\n            <tbody>\n              <tr>\n                <td>\n                  <div class=\"tcp-2ca905c4-bd21-4a37-b9ab-d2efdd465281\">\n                    <table class=\"table_WithBorder tcp-1d9100a4-04e5-4bf3-834b-f7356eec396c\">\n                      <tbody>\n                        <tr>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-5fed018f-bbc6-4552-a18c-aee1c78751c7\">Station 1</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-64706345-e20c-4520-9084-7fabb2668423\">Station 2</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-10059620-31cc-410b-97c8-171bb33883f4\">Station 3</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-8bd942b7-e974-4654-a99a-305e25f0706c\">Station 4</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-2336d0c4-386d-4f4c-a3eb-04da55c411fc\">Station 5</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-7dddefea-96ba-4ae8-a517-1587557c4a9e\">$3.699</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-4d4c7bb8-16fd-4ba1-a2cd-27b87cf836b3\">$3.609</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-005669da-8654-4c70-ac79-8db90a5de868\">$3.729</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-8b530509-992e-46e4-92f1-b50375448b29\">$3.679</td>\n                          <td class=\"tcp-8305b002-109a-4fbc-83ed-ed6506472e48\">$3.729</td>\n                        </tr>\n                      </tbody>\n                    </table>\n                  </div>\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n            </tbody>\n          </table>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">In the table above, Melissa recorded the price of one&nbsp;gallon of regular gas from five different local gas stations on the same day. What is the median of the gas prices Melissa recorded?</p>\n","answer":{"style":"Multiple Choice","choices":{"a":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$3.679</p>\n"},"b":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$3.689</p>\n"},"c":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$3.699</p>\n"},"d":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$3.729</p>\n"}},"correct_choice":"c","rationale":"<p>Choice C is correct. The median of a data set is the middle value when the data is in ascending or descending order. In ascending order, the gas prices are&nbsp;$3.609, $3.679, $3.699, $3.729, and $3.729. The middle number of this list is 3.699, so it follows that $3.699 is the median gas price.<p>Choice A is incorrect. When the gas prices are listed in ascending order, this value isn&rsquo;t the middle number.&nbsp;Choice B is incorrect. This value represents the mean gas price. Choice D is incorrect. This value represents both the mode and the maximum gas price.</p></p>\n"}}}